<ol xml:id="list-abstract-vec-spaces-activities-add-axioms" label="1.">
	<li xml:id="list-abstract-vec-spaces-activities-add-axioms-closed">
		The objects can be <em>added</em> (two at a time),
		and the resulting <q>sum</q> is always equal to another in the collection of objects.
	</li>
	<li xml:id="list-abstract-vec-spaces-activities-add-axioms-comm">
		Every <m>\uvec{v},\uvec{w}</m> satisfy <m>\uvec{w}+\uvec{v} = \uvec{v}+\uvec{w}</m>.
	</li>
	<li xml:id="list-abstract-vec-spaces-activities-add-axioms-assoc">
		Every <m>\uvec{u},\uvec{v},\uvec{w}</m> satisfy
		<m>\uvec{u}+(\uvec{v}+\uvec{w}) = (\uvec{u}+\uvec{v})+\uvec{w}</m>.
	</li>
	<li xml:id="list-abstract-vec-spaces-activities-add-axioms-zero">
		There is a special <term>zero object</term> in the collection,
		so that every <m>\uvec{v}</m> satisfies <m>\uvec{v}+\zerovec=\uvec{v}</m>.
	</li>
	<li xml:id="list-abstract-vec-spaces-activities-add-axioms-neg">
		Every <m>\uvec{v}</m> has an <term>opposite</term> <m>\widetilde{\uvec{v}}</m> so that
		<m>\uvec{v}+\widetilde{\uvec{v}}=\zerovec</m>.
	</li>
</ol>
